			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Becareful thinking that thief is going to make your rich.  Its true that farming (one way to make money) works out well for a thief.  And so does stealing and picking coffers.  But much of that doesn't work out well until you are 50.  If you want to farm with thief better than another job you'd need to be 45+.  Otherwise you can be another job and just sub thief while farming.  And for stealing really good beastcoins and picking coffers you need to be 50 and have a 25 RDM or WHM subjob.  Or you can sub ninja in the one castle where most of the mobs are sight only and use ninja powders ($$$) instead of casting magic.
<br />

<br />
Every form of money making in FF requires some investment to make it worth it.  Either farming (leveing thief), coffer picking (WHM/RDM sub to 25), mining (gear and picks, and researching best spots), fishing (fishing gear and time to raise you skill), tradeskills (raising the skill, researching what to make) they all require investment.  If the idea of stealing coins, mugging gil and getting higher rates of drops while farming is what you want to do, then thief is a decent way to make money.  But any job can make decent money if you invest the right amount of time and money.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
