				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">THF AF is highly useful in your 50s+ because of all the Steal+1.  Most of the pieces you will NOT use in an exp PT because there will be better stuff out there by the time you hit 60.  But you will carry it around w/ you whenever you try to steal from a mob.  Attaining your AF isn't overly difficult either.  Some of the pieces you can just "pop" the coffer without needing a key (which is what every other job has to do).  I've helped multiple THF with all AF related battles.  If you are a member of a good LS, you won't have to worry too much about getting your AF.
<br />

<br />
THF want high DEX and AGI with Accuracy as well.  Any gear you can pick up that have those modifiers are good.  Before level 33 when you get Viper Bite, most THF like to keep their dagger and sword skill capped.  Pre-33, you can Sneak Attack+Fast Blade to do some nice damage.  
<br />

<br />
I am not sure if this is true @ lower levels or not, but THF/NIN prefer the lowest delay weapons they can get.  THF damage comes from TP.  So, they faster they gain TP, the sooner they can unload a LOT of damage on a mob.  
<br />

<br />
If you are just starting out, a few of the top-end items may be out of your reach (Emperor Hairpin and Leaping Boots).  If you manage to save enough gil to purchase these early in your career as a THF, they will help immensely.  
<br />

<br />
When you level NIN, you need to do a couple things to make this work.  First, you need to raise your fame in Norg in order to attain the quest to get the Utsusemi:Ichi Scroll (Ninja Blink).  There are multiple ways to do this that isn't overly expensive.  Secondly, you want your NIN to have as much Evasion+ gear as possible.  Since NIN is one of the most expensive jobs in the game, you'll need to have a method of supporting yourself gil-wise.  Some people mention fishing, which is a good start.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
